<http://dx.doi.org/10.11646/zootaxa.3922.1.1>
    bibo:endPage "71" ;
    bibo:issue "1" ;
    bibo:journal "Zootaxa" ;
    bibo:startPage "1" ;
    bibo:volume "3922" ;
    dc:creator "Gómez-Zurita, Jesús" ;
    dc:date "2015" ;
    dc:title "Systematic revision of the genus Calligrapha Chevrolat (Coleoptera: Chrysomelidae, Chrysomelinae) in Central America: The group of Calligrapha argus Stål" ;
    fabio:hasPart <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3539686>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.287930>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.287937>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.287938> ;
    a fabio:JournalArticle .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3539686>
    dc:description "FIGURE 2. Distinguishing traits of major Calligrapha lineages: (a) connate claws of Calligrapha (Zygospila) mexicana Jacoby; (b) divergent claws of C. labyrinthica Stål; (c) unimpressed hypomera in C. percheroni Stål; (d) hypomera with impressed suture in C. argus Stål (white arrowhead); (e) habitus of C. californica Brown showing striped elytral pattern; (f) habitus of C. amelia Knab showing spotted elytra; (g) habitus of C. vigintimaculata (Chevrolat) showing reversed contrasting pattern of pale markings on dark background; (h) habitus of C. serpentina (Rogers) showing typical pattern of dark markings on pale background; (i) left elytron of C. sponsa Stål with a single spot enclosed by humeral lunule (white arrowhead); (j) left elytron of C. aladina Bechyné with arrangement of two spots enclosed by humeral lunule (white arrowheads); (k) left elytron of C. polyspila (Germar) with subhumeral (white arrowhead) and midlateral (black arrowhead) spots; and (l) left elytron of C. multipustulata Stål only with midlateral spot (black arrowhead)." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/3539686/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.287930>
    dc:description "FIGURE 1. Schematic representations of the typical apical ends of flagella in the penis of species in the Calligrapha argus group (a), in the C. dislocata and C. philadelphica groups (d), in the C. polyspila group (c), and in the C. labyrinthica group (d)." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/287930/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.287937>
    dc:description "FIGURE 9. Penis in ventral, lateral and dorsal view of apex of the species Calligrapha ancoralis Stål (a, d), C. anabelae sp. nov. (b, e), C. catarinae sp. nov. (c, f), C. ramulifera Stål (g, h), and C. argus Stål (i, j). Scale bar = 0.5 mm." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/287937/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.287938>
    dc:description "FIGURE 10. Geographic distributions of Calligrapha argus Stål (black circles) and C. ramulifera Stål (white circles)." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/287938/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

